  "prompt": "How is the word 'intimation' used in a sentence?",
  "response": "Certainly! Here are a few examples of how the word **\"intimation\"** can be used in a sentence:\n\n1. **Subtle Hint:**\n   - *She gave him an intimation that she might be interested in going to the concert together.*\n   \n2. **Indirect Communication:**\n   - *There was no direct refusal, only an intimation that the project might be postponed.*\n   \n3. **Suggestion or Indication:**\n   - *His sudden silence was an intimation that something was wrong.*\n\nIn these sentences, \"intimation\" refers to a hint, suggestion, or indirect indication of something.",
